content:
Add Routing Addresses for Email-to-Case

Set and configure routing addresses to redirect case submissions to the email services address provided by Salesforce. A case is created when the email address you specify is listed in the To, CC, or BCC fields of a customer email.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience
Available in: Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To configure routing addresses, you must have the following permissions:

* Setup and Configuration

To create a new routing address, click New Routing Address.

SETTING	DESCRIPTION
Routing Name	The name for the routing address—for example, Gold Support or Standard Support.
Email Address	The inbound email address for this Email-to-Case routing address. Emails sent to this address create cases using the specified settings.
Save Email Headers	Save the email routing information associated with each email submitted as a case.

Optional Settings:
Accept Email From	To limit the email addresses and domains that this routing address accepts, enter them here separated by commas.
Create Task from Email	When an email is submitted as a case, automatically create and assign a task to the Automated Case User specified on the Support Settings page.
Case Owner	(Optional) Select a user or queue to override the Default Case Owner specified on the Support Settings page.
Case Priority	The priority assigned to cases created from emails sent to this routing address.
Omni-Channel Flow	An active Omni-Channel flow that’s used to route cases when they’re created by Email-to-Case.
Fallback Queue	An Omni-Channel queue that uses Case as the service channel object.

Configure Routing Address Connection:

Connect and authenticate to an external Gmail or Outlook email server, or disconnect from a previously authenticated external account.

Before revoking access from a Gmail or Outlook account, first disconnect from the external account. Otherwise outgoing emails can’t be sent.
title: Configuring Service Cloud Routing Addresses
